Osun State Governor, Gboyega Oyetola, has called on members of the Igbo community resident in the state to support his re-election saying, “you are an important part of us.” He however assured the group that the government would continue to provide business-friendly environment for them. Oyetola, represented by his Special Assistant on Civic Engagement, Olatunbosun Oyinloye, stated this during an engagement meeting organised by the Civic Engagement Office in Osogbo with the newly-elected executives of Ohanaeze Ndigbo, Osun chapter on Thursday. He stressed the need for various ethnic groups to co-habit in peace, stressing that people of different tribes must feel secure in any part of the country they reside. “You are an important part of us in this state. And government will continue to provide the enabling environment for your businesses to grow. “Intolerance and insurgency will lead to poverty, hunger, unemployment, unrest, among others, and that is the reason we must continue to live together in peace. “Peaceful coexistence will bring stability, growth and make the economy vibrant, while the lack of it will bring underdevelopment and unrest,” Oyinloye said. He also appealed to Igbo community in the state to support Oyetola’s re-election in the July 16 governorship poll, so as to enable him consolidate on the achievements of the past years. The President of the apex Igbo group in the state, John Dike, while speaking at the event, commended the governor for ensuring peace and assured that members of the community would continue to live in peace with other tribes.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com